  <title translate="true">Motion Law Selector</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Segment Editor:<keyword translate="true">Motion-Law Selector</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Segment Editor: Motion-Law Selector</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading3 HowTo_atoc_"><text styleclass="Heading3 HowTo_atoc_" translate="true">Motion-Law Selector</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="AStandard" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">A Motion-Law is a mathematical function of how the motion-values vary during a segment.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">In the default Motion-Laws for each segment are Flexible-Polynomial. Their default settings are made so that they are equivalent to a </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Motion-Cam-Law-Polynomial345" styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">3-4-5 Polynomial</link><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">You have the option to select a different Motion-Law for each segment with the </text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">Motion-Law Selector</text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">Motion-Law Selector</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> is a &apos;drop-down box&apos; above the motion graphs.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">We recommend, to make </text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">the segments</text></para>
          <list id="5" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">All </text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">Flexible-Polynomials</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true"> - most powerful and flexible motion design possibilities</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">- OR -</text></para>
          <list id="6" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">All </text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">Traditional Motion-Laws</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true"> - &apos;standard&apos; motion-design requirements</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">- OR -</text></para>
          <list id="7" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">A mixture of Flexible-Polynomial and Traditional Motion-Laws - least preferred.</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Motion-Cam-Laws" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Motion-Laws</link><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> for the motion-Laws you can select.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:40px; background-color:#ccffcc;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="Toolbar-MotionLawSelector.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">To select a Motion-Law:</text></para>
          <list id="8" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;" translate="true">Click with your mouse above or below any graph, between two Blend-Points.</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;" translate="true">The segment that is above or below becomes the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Selected-Segment" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Active-Segment</link><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Blend-Point</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;" translate="true"> to the left-side of the </text><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true">Active-Segment</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:italic;" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;" translate="true">has the </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-weight:bold; color:#ff0000;" translate="true">RED</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; color:#ff0000;" translate="true">◊</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> &apos;diamond&apos; symbol.</text></para>
          <list id="9" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="2" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="HowTo Numbered" translate="true">Use</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> the drop-down </text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">Motion-Law Selector</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> to choose a different Motion-Law - see left.</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">You can also edit the Motion-Law with the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Segment-Editor" styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">Segment-Editor</link><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Numbered"></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
